    {
        protected override async Task<HandleRequestResult> HandleRemoteAuthenticateAsync()
        {
            // Build identity. Some code is omitted for clarity.
            var identity = new ClaimsIdentity(claims, CookieAuthenticationDefaults.AuthenticationScheme);
            var principal = new ClaimsPrincipal(identity);

            await Context.SignInAsync(CookieAuthenticationDefaults.AuthenticationScheme, principal, new AuthenticationProperties()
                {
                    IsPersistent = true
                });

             // Want to redirect to application endpoint since the user identity is established
             // variable "redirectURL" has value of "https://localhost/AspNetCoreSample/Sample/login" at this point but the location header of the response message (302) has a value of "/" in browser's message trace.
             Context.Response.Redirect(redirectUrl);

             return HandleRequestResult.Success(new AuthenticationTicket(principal, new AuthenticationProperties(), Scheme.Name));
        }
    }
```

## Background and Motivation

Kestrel (and other server impls) use the [PinnedBlockMemoryPool](https://github.com/dotnet/aspnetcore/blob/main/src/Shared/Buffers.MemoryPool/PinnedBlockMemoryPool.cs) for the core IO processing. The usage is purely internal today and also has the issue of never releasing its memory resulting in users thinking there is a memory leak. See: https://github.com/dotnet/aspnetcore/issues/55490

As part of wanting to reduce the memory when the pool is idle we want to use a timer, but creating a timer per pool is not ideal, so we want to put the cleanup on the kestrel heartbeat thread which requires sharing between Sockets, NamedPipes, and Kestrel Core. Ideally we want to avoid internals visible to, so in order to solve this we need a type that can be used by all dlls and shared via DI so we can wire up the pool usage everywhere.

## Proposed API

[Microsoft.AspNetCore.Connections.Abstractions.dll](https://github.com/dotnet/aspnetcore/tree/main/src/Servers/Connections.Abstractions/src/Features)

```diff
namespace Microsoft.AspNetCore.Connections;

+ public interface IMemoryPoolFactory
+ {
+    MemoryPool<byte> CreatePool();
+ }
```

## Usage Examples


```csharp
var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);

builder.Services.AddSingleton<IMemoryPoolFactory, MyMemoryPoolFactory>();

var app = builder.Build();

public sealed class MyMemoryPoolFactory : IMemoryPoolFactory
{
    public MemoryPool<byte> CreatePool()
    {
        return MemoryPool<byte>.Shared;
    }
}
```

## Alternative Designs

Alternatively we can use `[InternalsVisibleTo]` on some of our assemblies.

## Risks

